{"id": "2026-07-14-news-us-bombs-iran-a-third-consecutive-night-reinstat", "date": "2026-07-14", "stream": "news", "headline": "US bombs Iran a third consecutive night, reinstates naval blockade; Trump threatens Pickaxe Mountain nuclear site", "summary": "CENTCOM struck Bushehr, Bandar Abbas and other sites over five hours and reimposed a naval blockade; two UAE tankers were hit in Hormuz, killing one crew member; Trump threatened the Pickaxe Mountain nuclear facility.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/14/us-bombs-iran-again-tehran-strikes-gulf-tankers-whats-the-latest", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["ongoing"], "topics": ["geopolitics", "world"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "US forces bombed Iran for a third consecutive night into Tuesday 14 July and reimposed a naval blockade of Iranian ports, while Iranian missiles struck two UAE-flagged oil tankers in the Strait of Hormuz, killing one crew member. US Central Command said its latest raids began at 4:45pm ET Monday and ran for about five hours, hitting military targets at Bushehr, Chah Bahar, Jask, Konarak, Abu Musa and Bandar Abbas; Iran's Revolutionary Guard answered with fresh waves against Gulf targets, including US bases in Bahrain and Kuwait. The United Arab Emirates said two of its tankers were hit by Iranian cruise missiles in Omani waters, with one Indian crew member killed and eight people wounded. President Trump threatened to strike Pickaxe Mountain, an underground nuclear facility near Natanz, even as he insisted a deal was still possible, and floated charging vessels a fee to transit Hormuz. Oil hit a one-month high, with the strait now the war's central prize.", "why": "The conflict that opened on 28 February has hardened into a nightly bombing rhythm centred on the world's most important oil chokepoint, and the first confirmed tanker deaths mark a dangerous widening from military to civilian maritime targets.", "thread_id": "2026-06-20-cyber-papers-iran-closes-strait-of-hormuz-again-over-israeli", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-20", "event_date": "2026-07-14", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-14-news-hungarian-parliament-votes-to-end-pro-orban-pres", "date": "2026-07-14", "stream": "news", "headline": "Hungarian parliament votes to end pro-Orban president Tamas Sulyok's mandate", "summary": "Peter Magyar's Tisza used its two-thirds majority to pass a constitutional amendment ending Sulyok's term 139-6; Sulyok has five days to resign or sign.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/les-deputes-hongrois-se-prononcent-en-faveur-de-l-eviction-du-president-pro-orban-tamas-sulyok", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["politics", "world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Hungary's parliament passed a constitutional amendment on Monday 13 July ending the mandate of pro-Orban president Tamas Sulyok, the sharpest move yet by Prime Minister Peter Magyar to dismantle the machinery of the previous government. Magyar's centre-right Tisza party, which won a two-thirds super-majority in April, ending Viktor Orban's 16 years in power, pushed the change through 139 to 6; it ends Sulyok's term the day after it takes effect and lets parliament elect a successor. Sulyok, 70, whom Magyar has called an Orban puppet, has five days to resign or sign the amendment, and denounced a process he said violates the principles of the rule of law; Magyar has promised impeachment if he refuses, and Orban, in the US for the World Cup, urged Hungarians to resist a forced removal. The same amendment imposes term limits on lawmakers, restores the Constitutional Court's budget-oversight powers, sets an age-70 ceiling for its judges, and creates a national office to recover public assets lost to corruption.", "why": "It is the first real constitutional test of Hungary's post-Orban transition, and if Sulyok stalls it could tip into an open standoff between the presidency and a parliament determined to rewrite the rules Orban wrote.", "thread_id": "2026-07-14-news-hungarian-parliament-votes-to-end-pro-orban-pres", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-14", "event_date": "2026-07-13", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-14-news-ukraine-strikes-russian-refinery-1-400-km-from-t", "date": "2026-07-14", "stream": "news", "headline": "Ukraine strikes Russian refinery ~1,400 km from the front in the Urals; explosions over Kyiv overnight", "summary": "Ukrainian drones hit a refinery deep in Russia's Ural region, among the deepest strikes of the war, while Kyiv air defences engaged overnight.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/international/krieg-in-der-ukraine-ukraine-trifft-raffinerie-1400-kilometer-von-front-entfernt", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["ongoing"], "topics": ["geopolitics", "world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Ukrainian drones struck a Russian oil refinery some 1,400 km from the front line in the Ural region early Tuesday 14 July, among the deepest strikes of the war, as air defences engaged over Kyiv overnight. The hit extends Kyiv's months-long campaign against Russia's energy infrastructure to a target far beyond the usual range, part of a strategy to squeeze the fuel supply and revenue funding the war; SRF notes fuel shortages are now visibly biting Russian civilians. The overnight barrage on Kyiv, which the city's mayor said triggered its missile-defence systems, is a reminder that the exchange runs both ways with no ceasefire in view.", "why": "Reaching a refinery in the Urals shows Ukraine's long-range drone reach still growing, pushing the economic cost of the war deeper into the Russian interior even as its own capital stays under fire.", "thread_id": "2026-06-21-cyber-papers-ukraine-drone-strikes-hit-crimea-and-krasnodar-o", "first_seen_date": "2026-06-21", "event_date": "2026-07-14", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-14-news-mexico-s-sheinbaum-requests-us-criminal-charges", "date": "2026-07-14", "stream": "news", "headline": "Mexico's Sheinbaum requests US criminal charges over ICE deaths", "summary": "Mexico formally asked US state and federal prosecutors to bring charges after 17 Mexican nationals died in ICE raids or custody since Trump returned; it will also sue detention operators.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/14/mexicos-sheinbaum-announces-criminal-charges-request-in-us-over-ice-deaths", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["politics", "world"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Mexican President Claudia Sheinbaum said on Monday 13 July that her government is formally asking US prosecutors to bring criminal charges over the deaths of Mexican citizens in ICE (US Immigration and Customs Enforcement) operations and custody, the 17th such death coming with the 7 July shooting of Lorenzo Salgado Araujo in Houston. Sheinbaum said the complaints, lodged with both state and federal prosecutors, will target whoever is responsible for what Mexico deems homicides or rights violations, and that her government will also file civil suits against the private companies running ICE detention centres. She framed it as an escalation after diplomatic protest notes and a complaint to the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights produced no tangible progress, while stressing Mexico is not seeking conflict with Washington.", "why": "A foreign government asking US courts to prosecute US federal agents is an extraordinary step that pushes a domestic immigration-enforcement dispute into a bilateral diplomatic confrontation.", "thread_id": "2026-07-14-news-mexico-s-sheinbaum-requests-us-criminal-charges", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-14", "event_date": "2026-07-13", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-14-news-andalusia-wildfire-death-toll-reaches-13-nine-of", "date": "2026-07-14", "stream": "news", "headline": "Andalusia wildfire death toll reaches 13, nine of them foreigners", "summary": "Five Britons, three Belgians and a French national are among 13 killed in a southern Spain fire that burned 7,000 hectares since 9 July; now controlled.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/neuf-etrangers-parmi-les-13-victimes-dans-l-incendie-qui-a-ravage-le-sud-de-l-espagne", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source", "ongoing"], "topics": ["world"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "The wildfire in Andalusia, southern Spain, has now killed 13 people, nine of them foreigners, as autopsies identified five Britons, three Belgians, a French national and one Spaniard among the dead. The fire, sparked Thursday 9 July when a power cable fell along a road, tore through about 7,000 hectares of Mediterranean woodland at roughly 100 metres a minute before being brought under control; some bodies were so badly burned they had to be identified by DNA, and three victims remain unidentified. Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez, visiting the scene Monday, warned of a complicated summer and said last year Spain accounted for about a third of all the area burned in Europe.", "why": "One of Spain's deadliest fires in recent memory, striking foreign holidaymakers at the height of the season, underscores how longer, hotter European heatwaves are turning routine summers into lethal fire conditions.", "thread_id": "2026-07-10-news-wildfire-in-southern-spain-kills-at-least-11-wit", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-10", "event_date": "2026-07-09", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-14-news-federal-council-slowed-defence-minister-pfister", "date": "2026-07-14", "stream": "news", "headline": "Federal Council slowed Defence Minister Pfister's fast-track CHF 5bn air-defence buy", "summary": "An FOI-released draft shows Pfister wanted an urgent special army bill and a 2026 down payment for a second long-range air-defence system; the Federal Council refused the fast track.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/aufbau-der-luftverteidigung-wie-der-bundesrat-verteidigungsminister-martin-pfister-ausbremste", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland", "security"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "A freedom-of-information release shows Defence Minister Martin Pfister wanted to fast-track a second, longer-range air-defence system for CHF 5 billion, and that the Federal Council reined him in at its 24 June meeting. In a draft circulated to other departments before the session, Pfister argued Switzerland has no significant protection against long-distance attacks and an urgent need for the system, citing Russia's ramped-up arms production and a coming vulnerability window; he wanted a special army bill put to parliament right after the summer recess, a fast-track vote by December, and a down payment of well over CHF 1 billion this year, funded from unexpectedly high profit-tax revenue, to reserve production slots from 2027. Other departments' general secretaries sent critical feedback and Pfister backed off; the Council instead merely authorised talks with makers in France, South Korea and Israel, with no purchase date. The dispute sits atop already-spiralling costs for the ordered US Patriot system, where US options threaten to as much as triple the bill from CHF 2 billion to 6.3 billion unless Germany cedes a delivery originally meant for Switzerland.", "why": "It exposes an unusually public rift inside a normally consensual Federal Council over how fast and how much to spend rearming Switzerland, a debate the same 24 June meeting linked to a proposed VAT increase.", "thread_id": "2026-07-14-news-federal-council-slowed-defence-minister-pfister", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-14", "event_date": "2026-06-24", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-14-news-swiss-heatwave-to-ease-at-the-weekend-fribourg-w", "date": "2026-07-14", "stream": "news", "headline": "Swiss heatwave to ease at the weekend; Fribourg warns swimmers over water quality", "summary": "SRF Meteo says cooler air arrives at the weekend after another hot week; Fribourg canton warns of declining bathing-water quality.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/ende-der-hitzewelle-in-sicht-abkuehlung-kommt-am-wochenende", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland", "health"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "Relief from the heatwave is in sight: SRF Meteo says cooler air should reach Switzerland at the weekend after another sultry-to-hot week, while Fribourg canton warned swimmers of declining water quality. The coming days stay muggy and hot before the gradual change; the Fribourg environment office is advising people to use officially monitored bathing spots, one of a string of heat-driven measures around the country.", "why": "A concrete near-term forecast the local reader can plan around, and a small marker of the heat's knock-on effects on Swiss water and daily life.", "thread_id": "2026-07-14-news-swiss-heatwave-to-ease-at-the-weekend-fribourg-w", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-14", "event_date": null, "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-14-news-max-eiselin-who-led-the-1960-first-ascent-of-dha", "date": "2026-07-14", "stream": "news", "headline": "Max Eiselin, who led the 1960 first ascent of Dhaulagiri, dies at 94", "summary": "The Swiss mountaineering pioneer who organised the first ascent of the world's then seventh-highest peak died on 9 July.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/max-eiselin-pionnier-suisse-de-l-alpinisme-est-mort", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "Max Eiselin, the Swiss mountaineering pioneer who organised and led the 1960 first ascent of Dhaulagiri, has died at 94; a death notice published Tuesday 14 July said he died on 9 July. Eiselin masterminded the successful 1960 Swiss expedition to Dhaulagiri (8,167 m), then the world's seventh-highest peak and one of the last major unclimbed Himalayan summits, a feat remembered for its audacious logistics including a light aircraft ferrying gear onto the mountain.", "why": "He was one of the last links to Switzerland's golden age of Himalayan first ascents, a small but genuine piece of national sporting history.", "thread_id": "2026-07-14-news-max-eiselin-who-led-the-1960-first-ascent-of-dha", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-14", "event_date": "2026-07-09", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
